Write a SQL query that orders the items by price.

SELECT * FROM superstore
ORDER BY Price ASC;

Write your own SQL query that will show a statistic about the item prices, like a sum, average, minimum, maximum, or count.

SELECT SUM(price)
FROM superstore;


SELECT AVG(price)
FROM superstore;


SELECT MIN(price)
FROM superstore;

SELECT COUNT(price)
FROM superstore;

Write your own SQL query that will show a statistic about the price for items in the category of "Kitchen Supplies"

SELECT 
    category,
    SUM(price * stock_quantity)
FROM superstore
GROUP BY category
ORDER BY SUM(price * stock_quantity) DESC;


What is the total stock value (price × stock_quantity) for each category, and which category has the highest total stock value?

SELECT 
    category,
    SUM(price * stock_quantity)
FROM superstore
GROUP BY category
ORDER BY SUM(price * stock_quantity) DESC;


How many items are in the “Electronics” category?

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM superstore
WHERE category = 'Electronics';

 What is the cheapest item in the store, and how much does it cost?
 
SELECT item_name, price
FROM superstore
ORDER BY price ASC
LIMIT 1;
